summary: Mr Ramlal has called the ITC customer support several times regarding issues with his order, but his issues have not been resolved. He is frustrated that when he calls the support team, they are not helpful and do not seem to know what is going on with his order. He has three complaints, and the support team has not resolved any of them. He is asking for a manager to help him. The call continues as the agent tries to sort out his issues.
speaker_a_summary: Mr Ramlal is frustrated with the lack of support he has received for his three complaints. Monika, taking his call on her day off, checks the status of his previous complaints and informs him that one has been resolved and he should sign a document to formalise it in the presence of the district manager. She also informs him that a coupon, one of his other complaints, has been replaced and will be sent to him shortly. She arranges for priority treatment of his remaining complaint and promises a call within fifteen to twenty days. Mr Ramlal is satisfied with this resolution.
speaker_b_summary: Monika calls Ramal madam and informs her that she hasn't spoken to her in a long time. Monika denies receiving any goods from her. She hasn't talked to anyone and is not on vacation either. Monika informs her that she has received a complaint against her. She is frustrated that her slaves are not able to reach her and are not informed about her whereabouts. Monika is also facing problems due to the missing Tata number. She requests madam to resolve the issue as soon as possible.
cohere_points:
- Monika calls Mr Ramal to help him with his unresolved complaint, there has been a misunderstanding that has not been dealt with.
- There seem to be issues with the dispatch of goods and the communication within the company. 
- Mr Ramal has contacted the company multiple times and has not received a response. 
- They are currently trying to solve his issue and inform him about the progress. 
- Mr Ramal has previously spoken to Amit and Ajay about his complaint and they were not able to help him.
